        #### FULL WARNING NOT SUFFICIENTLY TESTED BEFORE LAUNCH REPORT ISSUES ON GITHUB ####
        ####################################################################################
        
        RELIGION CATEGORY PRECEPT SORTING DEFS
        =======================================
        
        These defs allow you to categorize precepts as Religion, Ideology, or Both.
        This controls whether a precept appears only in religion, only in ideology, or both.
        
        Category values:
            - "Religion"  = precept only appears in religion system
            - "Ideology"  = precept only appears in ideology system
            - "Both"      = precept appears in both systems
        
        Default (no entry): "Both" — all precepts appear in both systems by default.
        You only need to add entries if you want to RESTRICT a precept to one system.
        
        
        HOW TO MAKE A PATCH (for mod authors)
        ======================================
        
        If your mod adds custom precepts and you want to restrict them to one system,
        create an XML file in your mod's Defs/ directory with entries like this:
        
        <Defs>
            <IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryPreceptDef>
                <defName>CatPrecept_YourPreceptName</defName>
                <targetDefName>YourPreceptDefName</targetDefName>
                <category>Religion</category>
            </IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryPreceptDef>
        </Defs>
        
        The defName must be unique across all mods.
        The targetDefName must match your PreceptDef's defName exactly.
        
        Examples:
            "Religion" = prayer rituals, religious roles, spiritual practices
            "Ideology" = political policies, social norms, economic rules
            "Both"     = general moral beliefs that work in both contexts
        
        To modify an existing entry, use XML patching:
        
        <Defs>
            <IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryPreceptDef Name="CatPrecept_ExistingDef">
                <category>Both</category>
            </IdeoRework.ReligionCategoryPreceptDef>
        </Defs>
    -->
</Defs>
